# redirect-to-cn: domains that MUST exit via the China node (回国 / backcn).
#
# Format: one domain suffix per line. '#' comments and blank lines are ignored.
# Each target builder translates these into its own "route via CN node" rule:
#   Shadowrocket -> DOMAIN-SUFFIX,<d>,PROXY   (injected at the TOP of [Rule],
#                                              so it wins over GEOIP and the ad Reject list)
#   sing-box     -> (future) route rule -> cn outbound
#
# WHY these need to be explicit instead of relying on GEOIP,CN:
#   These services sit on global CDNs (Akamai / Tencent EdgeOne overseas nodes). When you
#   are abroad, DNS resolves them to a nearby *overseas* edge IP, so GEOIP,CN classifies
#   them as foreign and leaks them to DIRECT -> the app sees a foreign IP.
#   Routing by DOMAIN forces resolution + egress on the China node instead.
#   (Confirmed via Shadowrocket PacketTunnel log 2026-07-15: edith/www/fe-static/so/
#    pages/t2/sns-* .xiaohongshu.com / .xhscdn.com all hit FINAL,DIRECT before this fix.)

# 小红书 / RED / rednote
xiaohongshu.com
xhscdn.com
xhslink.com
xhs.cn
fegine.com
